    "body": "### Problem\n\nAdd this to your init.lua after setting up lsp\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({\"CursorHoldI\"},\n  callback = vim.lsp.buf.signature_help({\n    focusable = false,\n    focus = false,\n  })\n})\nThen when it opens:\nFirst \\<C-s> focuses the cursor inside the signature_help window and goes into normal mode.\nThen every consecutive \\<C-s> scrolls the signatures.\n\nThis feels very interuptive, because to scroll few signatures, you then have to leave the window and enter insert mode again to continue writing.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect signature_help window with focusable=false to scroll overloads without leaving insert mode and moving the cursor inside the signature_help window.",
